# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  ArtBloom backend environment variables
#  Copy this file to `.env` for local dev. In production (Render),
#  paste these into the Environment tab of the service — they're
#  marked `sync: false` in render.yaml so Render won't carry them over
#  from this repo.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Required ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Volcengine Ark API key (LLM, multimodal, image, video)
# Get one at https://console.volcengine.com/ark
ARK_API_KEY=

# ── Optional — model IDs (defaults in main.py are fine) ──────────────

# ARK_STORY_MODEL=doubao-seed-2-0-lite-260215
# ARK_CHAT_MODEL=doubao-seed-2-0-lite-260215
# ARK_VIDEO_MODEL=doubao-seedance-2-0-260128
# ARK_IMAGE_MODEL=doubao-seedream-5-0-260128

# ── Optional — production toggles ────────────────────────────────────

# Comma-separated origin list, or "*" for any origin.
# Defaults to localhost dev ports when unset.
# CORS_ALLOW_ORIGINS=*

# Cloudflare R2 public bucket URL serving textbook-assets/.
# When set, the in-process StaticFiles mount is skipped and the
# frontend resolves /textbook-assets/... URLs against this host.
# TEXTBOOK_ASSETS_URL=https://pub-xxxxxxxx.r2.dev

# ── Optional — Volcengine Speech (future TTS migration) ──────────────
#
# Current backend uses edge-tts (Microsoft) — these keys are unused
# today but stay documented so a future TTS port can pick them up.
# VOLCENGINE_SPEECH_API_KEY=
# VOLCENGINE_TTS_RESOURCE_ID=volcano_tts

# ── Required for per-user state persistence (R2) ─────────────────────
#
# 2026-05 — Per-invite-code state JSON blobs live in a Cloudflare R2
# bucket (S3-compatible). The endpoints in section 10 of main.py read
# /write `user-state/{INVITE_CODE}.json` so a teacher's workspace
# survives browser refreshes, device switches, and cache clears. If
# the variables below aren't set, `/api/state/*` returns 503 and the
# frontend falls back to localStorage-only persistence.
#
# How to provision:
#   1. Cloudflare dashboard → R2 → Create bucket `artbloom-user-state`
#      (any name works — match the R2_USER_STATE_BUCKET below).
#      Keep it private (no public r2.dev subdomain needed).
#   2. R2 → Manage R2 API Tokens → Create token with permission
#      "Object Read & Write" scoped to the bucket. Save the
#      Access Key ID / Secret Access Key pair.
#   3. R2 → bucket settings → Settings → S3 API endpoint shows
#      something like
#          https://<account-id>.r2.cloudflarestorage.com
#      Use the *jurisdiction-neutral* URL (no `.eu` / `.fedramp`).
#
# R2_ENDPOINT_URL=https://<account-id>.r2.cloudflarestorage.com
# R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
# R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
# R2_USER_STATE_BUCKET=artbloom-user-state
